abstract: >-
  bcqm_bundles is the reference implementation for Boundary-Condition Quantum
  Mechanics IV_d (BCQM IV_d). It simulates bundles of soft-rudder primitive
  threads, with optional shared-bias glue, to study how the centre-of-mass
  inertial noise amplitude scales with the coherence horizon W_coh and bundle
  size N. The repository provides the A-series (single-thread regression and
  independent bundles) and B-series (shared-bias bundles) runs used in the IV_d
  paper, together with analysis and figure-generation scripts.
